-- Noble, Delek Partnership to Start Drilling Leviathan (Correct)
-- B y   D a v i d   W a i n e r
-- 2010-10-18T08:25:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-18/noble-energy-delek-partnership-to-start-drilling-at-leviathan-site-today.html
(Corrects to say 453 billion cubic meters of gas.)  A partnership led by Noble Energy
Inc. and Delek Group Ltd. units is set to start exploration
drilling at the Leviathan site off Israel’s coast today,
according to an e-mailed statement from Delek.  The cost of the drilling will be $150 million, and the
site’s potential is 453 billion cubic meters of gas, the
statement said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
David Wainer in Tel Aviv at 
 dwainer1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
